The paper deals with the problem of approximating tensors, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of algebraic hypersurfaces and polynomial equations suggests a focus on computational algebraic geometry (cs.LG), while the application of the Perron-Frobenius theorem suggests numerical analysis (cs.NA) and scientific computing (cs.SI).
